    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-09-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-09-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="596" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d596">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Uhl</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Taylor</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-09-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 12,
                                    1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 186.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge receipt of your No.
                            227, of the 27th ultimo, and to approve your course in demanding of the
                            Spanish Government permission for the return of the missionaries to the
                            Caroline Islands.</p>
                <p>The draft for $17,500 which accompanied your No. 209, of July 13 last,
                            was duly received.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwin F. Uhl.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
